                "url": null,
                "found": "D:\\Vitmain\\backend\\requirements.txt"
            },
            "advisory": "Affected versions of the `urllib3` package are vulnerable to Denial of Service due to bypassed decompression-bomb safeguards in the streaming API. The `HTTPResponse.read(amt=N)` method, when used with the official Brotli library, decompresses the entire response instead of only the requested portion on subsequent calls, and `HTTPResponse.drain_conn()` also decodes the full response in a single operation after partial decompression. An attacker can exploit this by serving a highly compressed response, causing excessive CPU usage and massive memory allocation on the client, ultimately leading to resource exhaustion.",
            "is_transitive": false,
            "published_date": "2026-May-11",
            "fixed_versions": [
                "2.7.0"
            ],
            "closest_versions_without_known_vulnerabilities": [],
            "resources": [
