            "advisory": "Affected versions of the MessagePack for Python package are vulnerable to Denial of Service (DoS) due to improper handling of the `Unpacker` object after an error. The `Unpacker` fails to reset its internal state correctly when reused after encountering an error, leading to potential out-of-bounds reads. An attacker can exploit this vulnerability by providing malformed input to the `Unpacker`, causing the application to crash or become unresponsive, especially when processing untrusted data.",
